National Transportation Safety Board
Aviation Accident Final Report
Location: ENGLEWOOD, CO
Accident Number: DEN87LA078
Date & Time: 04/01/1987, 0955 MST
Registration: N114PA
Aircraft: Ercoupe (Eng & Research Corp.)
415C
Aircraft Damage: Substantial
Defining Event:
Injuries: 1 None
Flight Conducted Under: Part 91: General Aviation - Instructional
 Analysis THE STUDENT PLT SAID THE ACFT BALLOONED DURING THE FLARE AND HE APPLIED FORWARD STICK.
THE ACFT TOUCHED DOWN NOSE WHEEL FIRST AND THE NOSE GEAR COLLAPSED.
THE ACFT THEN SETTLED HARD ON MAIN GEAR RESULTING IN ADDITIONAL DAMAGE.
Probable Cause and Findings The National Transportation Safety Board determines the probable cause(s) of this accident to be: Findings Occurrence #1: HARD LANDING Phase of Operation: LANDING - FLARE/TOUCHDOWN Findings 1.
(C) FLARE - IMPROPER - PILOT IN COMMAND 2.
(C) FLIGHT CONTROLS - IMPROPER USE OF - PILOT IN COMMAND ---------- Occurrence #2: NOSE GEAR COLLAPSED Phase of Operation: LANDING - FLARE/TOUCHDOWN Findings 3.
